latestIgtvVideos.title: Weight loss meals ! Moong chhilka dal with palak
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Healthy , nutritious and mouth watering! 
Rice source of iron , calcium , fibre and protein 😋

Recipe 👇🏻 Ingredients
1 cup moong split dal ( moong dal chhilka ) 
2 cups water.
1 cup fresh spinach leaves, washed and chopped finely.
Salt to taste (1-1 1/2 tsp.)
1/2tsp. turmeric powder
2-3 tbs. mustard oil , can use desi ghee too 
1 tsp. cumin seeds
A large pinch of asafoetida or hing powder
1 medium sized chopped onion , 5-6 garlic cloves and 1 medium sized tomato 🍅 
½ tsp dhania (coriander powder)
½ tsp garam masala
½ red chilli powder 
Method & Instructions

Clean & wash dal.
Discard stems of palak. Chop the leaves finely. Wash the leaves.
Mix together dal, palak, salt & 3 cups water in a pressure cooker.
Pressure cook to give one whistle. Keep on low flame for eight minutes.
Heat oil in a small pan. Add jeera. Fry till golden.
Add chopped onions and garlic & cook till golden then , add tomato 
Cover the lid for 5 mins 
Add dhania powder, garam masala . Stir fry for 1-2 minutes.
Add the onion mixture to the palak. Mix well. Serve hot with rice.
.

latestPosts.caption:
Is it even possible to get your body back after kids ? 
Yes yes yes ! It’s possible my girls 🫶🏻
Follow @kurvesandkontours for more 
We are surrounded by myths and don’ts all around.
Mother in law says this ,, mother says that … my friend says this… Xyz nutritionist said that…. 🥺
The truth is to get your body back you only need to eat right , listen to your body and stay active. 
Start Immediately ‼️

Here are the things I followed post my daughters… 
1. I was active in 3 days ( yes I was doing all mine and my baby’s basics atleast ) never waited for anyone to even take my used plates back to the Kitchen. ( that helped me a lot in improving NEAT , weight jo chupke se lose hota hai )
#gradualbutconsistent 
2. I absolutely breast fed them , which additionally helped me loosing calories 
3. I was only consuming light vegetables like ghia , torai and only moong dal ( avoided rice , heavy legumes ) for first 40 days 
4. Ensured to take 2 boiled eggs in breakfast , lunch and evening 
5. I have a sweet tooth , so Panjiri was an add on but I compensated calories from Panjiri by reducing chapatis 😉
6. Used to take them on stroll for 40 mins in evening ( after 3 weeks )
7. Ensured that my bowel moments were absolutely healthy and not facing constipation ( major and important part which most of you ignore ) 
8. Was drinking a lot of ajwain water which was taking care of lactation part and helped me getting my menstrual cycles back in 40 days 
9. Avoided outside food as much as possible , because it was neither good for me nor for my child. 
10. Khichdi , daliya ( veg and milk ) was majorly part of my meals 

And that’s how I could get back to my pre baby body along with the flat stomach ( without using belt etc ) in just 8 weeks while #breastfeeding 🌸😇😘

If I can , even you can ! 
The more you delay the more it  becomes difficult for you to get back. Start asap ! 
Be wise eat right 

For any support, I am here , click the link in bio and start your journey now 

Also share with some one who needs to listen to this 😇
And don’t forget to follow @kurvesandkontours
